279
00:21:28,933 --> 00:21:30,767
Congratulations!

280
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:32,367
Thank you.

281
00:21:32,467 --> 00:21:34,933
Let's celebrate!

282
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:39,400
Congratulations, Naoki!

283
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:46,300
<i>Naoki is going to be a doctor!</i>

284
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,733
Kotoko!

285
00:21:56,533 --> 00:21:57,733
Excuse me.

286
00:22:01,267 --> 00:22:02,267
Mr. Irie!

287
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:09,300
It's not a bad offer. Think about it.

288
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:12,467
I will.

289
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:26,133
Well...

290
00:22:28,967 --> 00:22:30,600
What shall I do?

291
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:42,833
Oh, yes!

292
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:46,500
We'll have his graduation party
at home!

293
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:48,533
Sounds good!

294
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,733
I want to invite lots of people

295
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:54,567
so please invite your
nursing school friends.

296
00:22:55,567 --> 00:22:56,400
Oh, okay.

297
00:22:57,533 --> 00:23:00,300
Yuki, please invite Konomi.

298
00:23:01,167 --> 00:23:02,667
Why should I?

299
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:06,233
Because Konomi is your friend.

300
00:23:06,833 --> 00:23:09,033
She's not my friend.

301
00:23:09,133 --> 00:23:10,833
What do you mean?

302
00:23:10,933 --> 00:23:14,633
She made the top 100
in the final exams!

303
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,433
Ninety-seven.

304
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:17,367
What?

305
00:23:17,433 --> 00:23:19,300
Ninety-seven.

306
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:22,200
That's wonderful!

307
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,567
It's decided then!

308
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:27,400
I was a good tutor, that's why.

309
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:29,133
I see.

310
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:32,367
I felt the same way with Kotoko.

311
00:23:32,933 --> 00:23:38,333
It's a big deal for someone
in Class F to make the top 100.

312
00:23:38,433 --> 00:23:42,267
The power of love is amazing.

313
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:44,700
I told you! It was my tutoring.

314
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:46,600
The hardship of studying

315
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:50,833
was overcome by spending
time together and fostering love!

316
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:54,800
Now you and Konomi
have a special bond.

317
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:57,400
Kotoko! Shut up!

318
00:23:57,533 --> 00:23:59,200
But at the end of the day,

319
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:03,267
you wanted to be friends
with Konomi, too.

320
00:24:03,367 --> 00:24:05,267
I said...

321
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:09,267
When is Naoki's graduation?

322
00:24:10,567 --> 00:24:12,167
March 20th.

323
00:24:12,233 --> 00:24:16,767
I see. So he's going to be a doctor.

324
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:19,100
He's going to speak
on behalf of the graduates.

325
00:24:19,167 --> 00:24:20,133
Right, Naoki?

326
00:24:24,567 --> 00:24:26,700
What's wrong, Naoki?

327
00:24:30,500 --> 00:24:31,933
What?

328
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,033
You're speaking at
the graduation, right?

329
00:24:35,533 --> 00:24:36,400
Yeah.

330
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:37,433
I knew it!

331
00:24:37,533 --> 00:24:40,100
I'll bring my video camera!

332
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:42,100
Yuki is graduating, too.

333
00:24:42,167 --> 00:24:45,867
Maybe I should buy a new one!

334
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:49,300
Kotoko.

335
00:24:51,267 --> 00:24:54,733
I have something to tell all of you.

336
00:24:54,867 --> 00:24:57,533
What? You sound so serious.

337
00:24:58,333 --> 00:25:01,067
I met with my professor today.

338
00:25:01,933 --> 00:25:05,367
I'm thinking of working
at a hospital in Kobe.

339
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:13,433
Kobe.

340
00:25:14,133 --> 00:25:17,867
I thought you were going
to work at Tonan Hospital.

341
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:21,200
That's what I thought at first,

342
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:25,300
but I want to explore
some specialized fields

343
00:25:26,833 --> 00:25:28,167
But...

344
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:31,867
The hospital in Kobe
is very specialized.

345
00:25:31,967 --> 00:25:33,900
But! But...

346
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,667
Kobe is so far!

347
00:25:37,767 --> 00:25:40,667
It's 6 hours there and back. How...?

348
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:43,467
Commuting is unreasonable.

349
00:25:43,567 --> 00:25:45,767
Then...

350
00:25:46,133 --> 00:25:49,700
I'm thinking of moving to Kobe.

351
00:25:51,767 --> 00:25:55,233
Naoki! Are you serious?

352
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:57,867
Yeah.

353
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:01,500
I've already been invited
by a doctor in Kobe.

354
00:26:02,333 --> 00:26:07,200
I'd study there for a few years
and then return.

355
00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:11,167
Naoki! Then...

356
00:26:11,267 --> 00:26:15,400
I have to find a school in Kobe!
Do I have time?

357
00:26:15,467 --> 00:26:17,067
You should stay.

358
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:22,633
I'll go on my own.

359
00:26:22,733 --> 00:26:26,567
You should stay here
and continue your studies.

360
00:26:29,767 --> 00:26:33,067
I don't want to be apart!

361
00:26:33,767 --> 00:26:39,100
Study here for a year
and come after you graduate.

362
00:26:39,233 --> 00:26:43,800
No! I don't want to be
apart for a whole year!

363
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:46,500
I'm not that smart!

364
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:50,700
What if I don't graduate next year?
Then, it will be longer!

365
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:51,800
Kotoko.

366
00:26:51,867 --> 00:26:55,733
We'll be apart for too long!
I can't do it!

367
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:59,300
Do you expect me to wait
until you become a nurse

368
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:00,867
and then go to Kobe?

369
00:27:01,500 --> 00:27:03,767
How could you say that, Naoki?

370
00:27:03,833 --> 00:27:08,100
Think how Kotoko feels.
You're husband and wife!

371
00:27:08,167 --> 00:27:09,000
Yeah.

372
00:27:09,067 --> 00:27:10,767
You shouldn't be apart!

373
00:27:11,433 --> 00:27:15,000
Don't just think about yourself.

374
00:27:15,067 --> 00:27:16,433
I know.

375
00:27:18,167 --> 00:27:19,533
You don't know.

376
00:27:21,567 --> 00:27:23,333
You wouldn't understand.

377
00:27:26,167 --> 00:27:31,200
Because I love you way more
than you love me.

378
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,333
You wouldn't know

379
00:27:34,267 --> 00:27:35,267
how I feel.

380
00:27:35,867 --> 00:27:39,067
How hard it would be
to be apart from you!

381
00:27:41,967 --> 00:27:42,933
Because

382
00:27:47,567 --> 00:27:48,467
you

383
00:27:51,133 --> 00:27:54,133
would be totally fine without me.

384
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,167
When you made your decision

385
00:28:04,167 --> 00:28:05,200
you never

386
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:08,933
even thought about me, did you?

387
00:28:13,833 --> 00:28:16,500
I'm the only one that would miss you!

388
00:28:19,933 --> 00:28:21,167
Kotoko.

389
00:28:34,733 --> 00:28:35,667
<i>What should I do...?</i>

390
00:28:36,767 --> 00:28:39,567
<i>What should I do? What?</i>

391
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,800
<i>I'm making it hard for him.</i>

392
00:28:47,367 --> 00:28:50,733
<i>I'm failing him as his wife.</i>

393
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:54,767
<i>I know. I know it.</i>

394
00:28:56,467 --> 00:28:59,000
<i>But... But...</i>

395
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:04,567
<i>I don't want to be apart.</i>

396
00:29:34,967 --> 00:29:35,833
Kotoko.

397
00:29:40,300 --> 00:29:42,767
You didn't eat dinner again?

398
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:45,867
No.

399
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:48,033
But I'm sleepy.

400
00:29:50,233 --> 00:29:51,067
Kotoko.

401
00:29:51,167 --> 00:29:52,333
Good night.

402
00:30:15,533 --> 00:30:16,500
Welcome home.

403
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:20,367
Thanks. You're still up?

404
00:30:21,567 --> 00:30:24,600
Do you have a minute, dad?

405
00:30:34,367 --> 00:30:37,700
How's Kotoko? Is she still upset?

406
00:30:38,367 --> 00:30:39,467
Yes.

407
00:30:39,567 --> 00:30:43,800
I was prepared for a bad reaction, but

408
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:48,400
when I actually see her like this...

409
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:55,133
She's crazy about you, that's why.

410
00:30:57,667 --> 00:30:58,733
Dad.

411
00:30:59,533 --> 00:31:02,400
I'm thinking of taking
Kotoko to Kobe with me.

412
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:06,300
Naoki... But...

413
00:31:06,933 --> 00:31:11,833
If we find a nursing school now
she might be able to transfer.

414
00:31:13,133 --> 00:31:14,067
But...

415
00:31:14,933 --> 00:31:18,467
she won't know anyone
in a strange, new city.

416
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,667
Will she be able
to settle down and study?

417
00:31:23,367 --> 00:31:27,100
I'll probably be so busy myself...

418
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,500
I wasn't confident

419
00:31:30,100 --> 00:31:34,300
that I could think about
her well being, too.

420
00:31:37,133 --> 00:31:39,633
I want her to become a nurse.

421
00:31:40,933 --> 00:31:42,000
I thought

422
00:31:42,667 --> 00:31:46,367
it may be better for us
to spend a year apart.

423
00:31:48,267 --> 00:31:49,600
Naoki.

424
00:31:52,767 --> 00:31:53,667
She

425
00:31:54,833 --> 00:31:56,400
doesn't seem to realize

426
00:31:58,033 --> 00:31:59,567
that I love her.

427
00:32:23,133 --> 00:32:24,333
<i>Naoki.</i>

428
00:32:46,767 --> 00:32:48,233
Representing the undergraduates,

429
00:32:48,733 --> 00:32:50,500
Takayuki Miura of the Medical School.

430
00:32:57,067 --> 00:33:00,533
Address by Naoki Irie
of the Medical School.

431
00:33:00,867 --> 00:33:02,000
Yes.

432
00:33:18,700 --> 00:33:19,967
Farewell address.

433
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:23,967
When I look back on my life
at Tonan University,

434
00:33:24,667 --> 00:33:30,800
many unforgettable memories
come to mind.

435
00:33:31,833 --> 00:33:36,833
<i>How did I feel watching Naoki</i>
<i>at our high school graduation?</i>

436
00:33:42,600 --> 00:33:47,500
<i>Jinko, Satomi and Kin-chan were there.</i>

437
00:33:49,333 --> 00:33:52,333
<i>Naoki refused to give me his button.</i>

438
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:03,467
<i>But I still feel the same way.</i>

439
00:34:04,333 --> 00:34:05,833
<i>I love Naoki!</i>

440
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:11,067
<i>All I know is one thing.</i>
<i>That I love Naoki.</i>

441
00:34:11,967 --> 00:34:15,400
Representing the graduates
of the Medical School ...

442
00:34:16,200 --> 00:34:17,400
Naoki Irie.

443
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:33,533
<i>That's one thing</i>
<i>that will never change.</i>

444
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:48,133
This is the engineering campus
he attended as a freshman.

445
00:34:49,633 --> 00:34:51,700
Yuko Matsumoto was here, too.

446
00:34:53,133 --> 00:34:54,800
Did you decide on your electives?

447
00:34:55,567 --> 00:34:56,467
No, not yet.

448
00:35:04,967 --> 00:35:07,033
And the Tennis Club.

449
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:10,667
We played a doubles match.

450
00:35:16,100 --> 00:35:17,100
Smooth.

451
00:35:29,233 --> 00:35:31,500
The cafeteria where we ate lunch

452
00:35:33,700 --> 00:35:35,367
and Naoki fought with Kin-chan.

453
00:35:37,967 --> 00:35:39,267
What's with these portions?

454
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:41,433
Got a problem with it?

455
00:35:43,567 --> 00:35:44,400
Kin-chan?

456
00:35:50,733 --> 00:35:52,433
The medical lecture hall.

457
00:35:53,467 --> 00:35:56,233
I used to watch Naoki from here.

458
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:58,000
There he is!

459
00:35:58,433 --> 00:36:02,000
His aura outshines everyone else.

460
00:36:02,500 --> 00:36:03,633
Yes!

461
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:11,333
<i>I won't be seeing him here anymore.</i>

462
00:36:12,833 --> 00:36:14,267
Naoki.

463
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:17,933
Naoki.

464
00:36:21,033 --> 00:36:23,067
Naoki!

465
00:36:25,900 --> 00:36:27,200
What?

466
00:36:29,733 --> 00:36:31,433
You're so loud.

467
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:34,067
How did you...?

468
00:36:34,233 --> 00:36:36,733
I thought you might be here.

469
00:36:38,900 --> 00:36:40,400
I have to talk to you.

470
00:36:41,433 --> 00:36:43,033
It's probably better to talk here.

471
00:36:45,567 --> 00:36:46,867
About Kobe.

472
00:36:46,967 --> 00:36:47,933
I...!

473
00:36:52,767 --> 00:36:53,700
I...

474
00:36:55,067 --> 00:36:57,067
I'll become a nurse in one year.

475
00:36:58,433 --> 00:36:59,800
Then I'll go to Kobe.

476
00:37:01,500 --> 00:37:04,567
I promise! So...

477
00:37:08,033 --> 00:37:09,100
Wait for me.

478
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:13,500
Don't

479
00:37:14,733 --> 00:37:15,800
cheat on me.

480
00:37:19,633 --> 00:37:21,533
Don't get mad

481
00:37:22,967 --> 00:37:24,600
if I call you every day.

482
00:37:25,667 --> 00:37:27,567
And...

483
00:37:29,567 --> 00:37:30,867
And?

484
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:36,667
On my breaks

485
00:37:37,333 --> 00:37:38,567
I'll come

486
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:53,933
Someone might come.

487
00:37:57,867 --> 00:38:00,633
I don't care.

488
00:38:43,367 --> 00:38:44,400
This is fine.

489
00:38:44,500 --> 00:38:46,700
I'll see you off at the station.

490
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:48,233
That's okay.

491
00:38:48,333 --> 00:38:52,433
You might stop the bullet train
if you come to see me off.

492
00:38:52,533 --> 00:38:54,733
No I won't...

493
00:38:56,533 --> 00:38:57,667
But...

494
00:38:58,100 --> 00:39:02,567
maybe it will be easier
to say good-bye here.

495
00:39:03,333 --> 00:39:05,867
Yeah. See you.

496
00:39:09,500 --> 00:39:12,567
Call me when you get there.

497
00:39:12,633 --> 00:39:13,467
Sure.

498
00:39:13,567 --> 00:39:16,300
Your lunch.

499
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:18,067
I'll buy one!

500
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:24,800
Shin-Kobe is one station
after Okayama. Don't miss it!

501
00:39:24,900 --> 00:39:27,133
You mean after Shin-Osaka.

502
00:39:39,233 --> 00:39:42,867
Can I go now?

503
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:45,633
Sure.

504
00:39:46,933 --> 00:39:49,467
How about a good-bye kiss?

505
00:39:51,900 --> 00:39:53,400
Just joking.

506
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:00,600
Study hard.

507
00:40:01,433 --> 00:40:04,600
You too, Naoki!

508
00:40:04,700 --> 00:40:05,900
Yeah.

509
00:40:56,267 --> 00:40:58,933
You can do it, Naoki!

510
00:41:19,500 --> 00:41:21,367
You can do it, Kotoko.

511
00:41:23,267 --> 00:41:24,367
We can...

512
00:41:25,267 --> 00:41:26,200
do it.

513
00:42:55,600 --> 00:42:56,433
{\an8}<i>Next Episode</i>
<i>Ep.12 "...and Love in KOBE"</i>

514
00:42:56,500 --> 00:42:57,933
{\an8}<i>How much bandage do you need?</i>

515
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:02,133
{\an8}I haven't talked to Naoki
in three days!

516
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:04,333
<i>1,000 yen that she'll go to Kobe</i>
<i>within a week.</i>

517
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,500
<i>5,000 yen that she'll leave tomorrow.</i>

518
00:43:06,567 --> 00:43:07,667
I did it...!

519
00:43:09,933 --> 00:43:10,900
There he is!

520
00:43:10,967 --> 00:43:14,133
<i>I'm feeling more energized</i>
<i>every minute.</i>

521
00:43:14,200 --> 00:43:16,267
<i>He might start feeling single again</i>

522
00:43:16,333 --> 00:43:18,633
<i>and spread his wings.</i>

523
00:43:18,700 --> 00:43:19,533
I found you!

524
00:43:20,233 --> 00:43:21,067
{\an8}Kotoko.

525
00:43:21,133 --> 00:43:23,000
{\an8}The mother and daughter
are named Shiina.

526
00:43:23,067 --> 00:43:25,433
{\an8}DISCLAIMER:
THIS DRAMA IS A WORK OF FICTION

527
00:43:25,500 --> 00:43:28,467
